issue.title: Library should implement SLA-compliant retry policies

labels.name: priority: p3
labels.description: Desirable enhancement or fix. May not be included in next release.

labels.name: type: feature request
labels.description: ‘Nice-to-have’ improvement, new feature or different behavior or design.

labels.name: api: firestore
labels.description: Issues related to the googleapis/nodejs-firestore API.

issue.body:
Thanks for stopping by to let us know something could be better!

**PLEASE READ**: If you have a support contract with Google, please create an issue in the [support console](https://cloud.google.com/support/) instead of filing on GitHub. This will ensure a timely response.

 **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**

We have had a few instances where Firestore requests began failing en masse, as described here:
https://github.com/firebase/firebase-admin-node/issues/1903

In one case we had an hour-long outage. I contacted Google Cloud support to say that this is an SLA violation (we use Cloud Firestore multi-regional) but their response was that it is my responsibility to retry this kind of failure and therefore the SLA was not violated.

 **Describe the solution you'd like**

Official client libraries like this one should implement Google-recommended best practices for handling retryable errors. It would be one thing if I was using the HTTP or gRPC API directly, but because I am using this Googler-maintained client library I was not expecting to have to add my own error handling for very uncommon gRPC error codes like `2 UNKNOWN` and I did not learn about this expectation until our business had already had a major outage.

 **Describe alternatives you've considered**

I could do this myself, but this would mean wrapping all Firestore calls in paranoid retry loops.

 **Additional context**

N/A

comment.body: @cherylEnkidu Is there an update on this? Will the fix you reference be added to this library? We just started to experience this error today on code that is unchanged and previously working without error for weeks. Thanks.

issue.body:
The documentation for the create method could be improved to explain exactly what "The write fails if the document already exists " means. Will the call throw an error ? If so it's not listed in throws. If it does nothing, then it should say it does nothing instead of "fails".

```ts
    /**
     * Creates a document referred to by this `DocumentReference` with the
     * provided object values. The write fails if the document already exists
     *
     * @param data The object data to serialize as the document.
     * @throws Error If the provided input is not a valid Firestore document.
     * @return A Promise resolved with the write time of this create.
     */
    create(data: WithFieldValue<T>): Promise<WriteResult>;
```

issue.title: Update google-gax dependency to 4.x.x for @google-cloud/firestore 6.x.x

labels.name: priority: p3
labels.description: Desirable enhancement or fix. May not be included in next release.

labels.name: type: feature request
labels.description: ‘Nice-to-have’ improvement, new feature or different behavior or design.

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**

google-gax has a couple of dependencies that should be devDependencies. The most problematic being a (prod) dependency on protobufjs-cli, which pulls in jsdoc, (all of) lodash, and a couple of others, for a total of about 7MB of unnecessary dependencies. 

@google-cloud/firestore 6.x.x currently depends on google-gax 3.x.x. I realize this is no longer the case in @google-cloud/firestore 7.x.x, but there are many packages that still depend on @google-cloud/firestore  6.x.x.

My chain of (prod) dependencies is `firebase-admin > @google-cloud/firestore > google-gax > protobufjs-cli`

 **Describe the solution you'd like**
Bump the version of google-gax to to 4.x.x 

 **Describe alternatives you've considered**
Bumping the version of @google-cloud/firestore in firebase-admin, but @google-cloud/firestore 6.x.x > 7.x.x seems like a bigger change than the google-gax change.

 **Additional context**
None
